msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 26"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "26. Cīvarasibbanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on sewing robes"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.61"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.26.1"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.285"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="575"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

#. VAR: āyasmā udāyī paṭṭo → udāyi paṭṭo (bj) | udāyi paṭṭho (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī paṭṭo hoti cīvarakammaṃ kātuṃ."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Udāyī had become skilled in making robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Aññatarā bhikkhunī yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Just then a certain nun approached Udāyī"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "“sādhu me, bhante, ayyo cīvaraṃ sibbatū”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, would you please sew me a robe?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <i lang="pli">Paṭibhānacittaṃ</i>. <i lang="pli">Citta</i> is here equivalent to Sanskrit <i lang="pli">citra</i>, which means colorful, variegated, decorative, etc., and by extension it also means a picture or painting, which seems to be the intended meaning here. <i lang="pli">Paṭibhāna</i> means something like impromptu imagination. The commentary, <ref>Sp.4.804.29</ref>, specifies that it was a picture of a couple having sexual intercourse. 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā udāyī tassā bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbitvā surattaṃ "
"suparikammakataṃ katvā majjhe paṭibhānacittaṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā saṃharitvā "
"nikkhipi."
msgstr ""
"He then sewed a robe for that nun, making it beautiful and nicely dyed, and "
"he drew an imaginative picture in the middle of it. He then folded it and "
"put it aside."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "Atha kho sā bhikkhunī yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Soon afterwards that nun went to Udāyī"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "“kahaṃ taṃ, bhante, cīvaran”ti?"
msgstr "“Venerable, where’s the robe?”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.286"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.10"
msgid ""
"“Handa, bhagini, imaṃ cīvaraṃ yathāsaṃhaṭaṃ haritvā nikkhipitvā yadā "
"bhikkhunisaṃgho ovādaṃ āgacchati tadā imaṃ cīvaraṃ pārupitvā "
"bhikkhunisaṃghassa piṭṭhito piṭṭhito āgacchā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Now, Sister, take this robe as it’s folded and put it aside. When the Order "
"of nuns goes to the instruction, then put it on and follow right behind the "
"other nuns.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā bhikkhunī taṃ cīvaraṃ yathāsaṃhaṭaṃ haritvā nikkhipitvā yadā "
"bhikkhunisaṃgho ovādaṃ āgacchati tadā taṃ cīvaraṃ pārupitvā "
"bhikkhunisaṃghassa piṭṭhito piṭṭhito āgacchati."
msgstr "And that nun did just that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized her,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.13"
msgid ""
"“yāva chinnikā imā bhikkhuniyo dhuttikā ahirikāyo, yatra hi nāma cīvare "
"paṭibhānacittaṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How wanton these nuns are, how brazen and shameless, in that they draw "
"pictures on their robes.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="576"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "And the nuns asked her,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "“kassidaṃ kamman”ti?"
msgstr "“Who did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "“Ayyassa udāyissā”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable Udāyī.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.17"
msgid ""
"“Yepi te chinnakā dhuttakā ahirikā tesampi evarūpaṃ na sobheyya, kiṃ pana "
"ayyassa udāyissā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“This sort of work would not even make those who are wanton, brazen, and "
"shameless look good, let alone Venerable Udāyī.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="577"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The nuns told the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.21"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbissatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī sew a robe for a nun?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.24"
msgid "“Ñātikā te, udāyi, aññātikā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is she a relative of yours?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.25"
msgid "“Aññātikā, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.26"
msgid ""
"“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātikāya na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā "
"pāsādikaṃ vā apāsādikaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"“Foolish man, a man and a woman who are not related don’t know what’s "
"appropriate and what’s inappropriate in dealing with each other, what’s "
"inspiring and what’s not."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.27"
msgid ""
"Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbissasi."
msgstr "And still you sewed a robe for an unrelated nun."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.29"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.29a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="578"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.30"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbeyya vā sibbāpeyya vā, "
"pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk sews a robe for an unrelated nun, or gets one sewn, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs1.31"
msgid "(<em>26</em>:<strong>75</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.26.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.26.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="579"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="580"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "Aññātikā nāma"
msgstr "Unrelated:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.287"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddhā."
msgstr ""
"anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven "
"generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="581"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "A nun:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "she has been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="582"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "A robe:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. The six are linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp; see <ref>Mv.8.3.1</ref>. 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ."
msgstr "one of the six kinds of robes."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.62"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="583"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Sibbeyyāti"
msgstr "Sews:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "sayaṃ sibbati ārāpathe ārāpathe āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"if he sews it himself, then for each stitch he commits an offense entailing "
"confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="584"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "Sibbāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Gets sewn:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukampi sibbati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he only asks once, then even if the other sews many times, he commits one "
"offense entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.26.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="585"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid ""
"Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī cīvaraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he sews her a "
"robe or gets one sewn, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid ""
"Aññātikāya vematiko cīvaraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If she is unrelated, but he is unsure if she is, and he sews her a robe or "
"gets one sewn, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Aññātikāya ñātikasaññī cīvaraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If she is unrelated, but he perceives her as related, and he sews her a robe "
"or gets one sewn, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="586"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Ekatoupasampannāya cīvaraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he sews a robe, or gets one sewn, for a nun who is fully ordained only on "
"one side, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "Ñātikāya aññātikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If she is related, but he perceives her as unrelated, he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Ñātikāya vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If she is related, but he is unsure if she is, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid "Ñātikāya ñātikasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If she is related and he perceives her as related, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.26.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="587"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "ñātikāya,"
msgstr "if she is related;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "cīvaraṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he sews any requisite apart from a robe, or gets it sewn;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "sikkhamānāya,"
msgstr "if it is a trainee nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "sāmaṇeriyā,"
msgstr "if it is a novice nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="588"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:pts-cs2.3.8"
msgid "Cīvarasibbanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "The sixth rule, the training rule on sewing robes, is finished."

